{
  "risk_rating": "low",
  "short_description": "The inbound webhook HMAC authenticates only a static, per-org identifier carried in the URL path and is never bound to the request body, the object-resolution key, a timestamp, or a nonce. The resulting value is a deterministic, replayable per-org bearer secret: a single leaked webhook URL grants permanent, reusable forged-payload access until the secret is rotated.",
